cs.MA, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.IT, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new method for learning network state parameters using inverse optimization models and supporting algorithms. The focus is on transportation networks and the behavior of heterogeneous travelers. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). The paper also involves statistical inference and optimization, which suggests categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.RO (Robotics). The use of inverse optimization models and algorithms also suggests categories such as cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
